President Trump delivered remarks at a roundtable discussion in White Sulphur Springs, West Virginia, where he praised the state's economic progress and highlighted the positive impact of the tax cuts. He emphasized the need to address trade imbalances with China and the European Union, and spoke about his administration's efforts to combat the opioid epidemic and strengthen border security. The President also heard from individuals and businesses who have benefited from the tax cuts, including increased wages and bonuses.